  "featured_insight": {
    "headline": "v3.2 Gem Primary goes 3/3 on NBA Playoff showdowns",
    "subhead": "New max-val-in-$6K-pool rule nails Chet Holmgren, Tobias Harris, and Deni Avdija \u2014 all three land in winning lineups.",
    "body": "Across three NBA Game-3 through Game-6 showdown slates on 4/19, OverOwned's new v3.2 Gem Primary formula flagged Chet Holmgren (PHX@OKC), Tobias Harris (ORL@DET), and Deni Avdija (POR@SAS) as the highest-value plays in the $6K+ pool. All three landed in bgreseth's winning lineups \u2014 Chet as CPT (49.88 pts), Tobias as UTIL (34.0 pts), and Avdija as CPT (83.25 pts). Secondary Trap also went 3/3 correctly fading punt-tier max-val plays (Maluach, da Silva, Murray). Primary Trap went 0/3 \u2014 all three dominant stars (SGA, Cade, Wemby) ended up in winners, a structural pattern on star-dominated showdown slates.",
